{"title":"The Silence Has A Stopping Rule","idea_type":"model","source_basis":["Thinking method source: notes/source-cards/daoism-dao-de-jing-chapter-48.md on learning by decrease and wu wei. I applied decrease by subtracting the urge to find one shared essence, then asking where each practice tells inquiry to change form.","Method critique source: notes/source-cards/early-buddhism-mn-1-mulapariyaya-sutta.md on conceiving experience. It checked the Daoist lens by warning that even a clean stopping rule can become another thing the comparer owns.","notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-brihadaranyaka-upanishad-3-7-23.md and notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-shankara-upadesa-sahasri.md as witness-side sources where the knower resists objectification.","notes/source-cards/early-buddhism-sn-22-59-anattalakkhana-sutta.md and notes/source-cards/early-buddhism-sn-22-95-phenapindupama-sutta.md as sources where no aggregate is fit to be taken as self or final ground.","notes/source-cards/daoism-zhuangzi.md as a Daoist source for fasting the heart-mind, self-forgetting, and non-ontological transformation.","notes/source-cards/sufism-al-ghazali-the-alchemy-of-happiness.md as a relational source where self-knowledge, God-knowledge, remembrance, and love resist reduction to detached observation.","notes/source-cards/neoplatonism-plotinus-enneads-fifth-ennead.md as a unity and return source where dispersion from the One frames the danger of multiplicity.","Prior Codex findings: Translation Strain as a Load Test for Convergence, Negation Has An Address, Return Is the Audit, Each Path Has a Different Alarm, and The Comparison Has A Self.","Prior Claude findings: The Inferential Gap, The Instrument Problem, The Epistemic Organ, The Shadow of Attainment, and The Verification Architecture."],"original_claim":"A tradition's inquiry is shaped by its stopping rule: the moment a method tells the practitioner that the next move would distort rather than clarify. Advaita stops objectifying at the non-objectifiable knower. Early Buddhism stops granting ownership to any aggregate, state, or insight. Daoism stops when deliberate control reappears. Sufism stops when self-possession interrupts remembrance and love. Neoplatonism stops when attention scatters from unity into mere multiplicity. These rules make different silences feel final. They sit between instrument and inference: before a tradition argues what silence means, it has trained the practitioner where inquiry should cease, continue, or change form.","why_it_might_be_new":"This adds a variable not covered by the current Lumenary models. The instrument problem asks how practice generates data. Inferential gap asks what conclusions are drawn. Alarm profile asks what error feels dangerous. Verification architecture asks who can certify success. Stopping rule asks where the method withdraws permission to keep using the same kind of inquiry. It explains why similar quieting or de-identification can harden into different claims without treating convergence as proof or disagreement as mere translation failure.","critique":"The model may make living traditions look too procedural. Many practices do not simply stop inquiry; they ripen it, redirect it, or embed it in ethics, devotion, ritual, and teacher relationship. The Daoist decrease lens helped prevent forced convergence, but it may overvalue cessation and underweight constructive disciplines. The Buddhist critique also applies to this model itself: calling something a stopping rule may be the researcher's own act of conceiving. The idea should be weakened if primary manuals show that these stopping points vary more by stage, teacher, and institution than by tradition.","epistemic_labels":["textual","interpretive","phenomenological","empirical-adjacent","analogical","speculative"],"scores":{"novelty":0.81,"generativity":0.88,"cross_tradition_support":0.69,"logical_coherence":0.85,"explanatory_compression":0.84,"empirical_adjacency":0.43,"practice_testability":0.75,"counterargument_quality":0.84,"source_reliability":0.66,"publishability":0.82},"next_research_directions":["Build a stopping-rule rubric with fields for prohibited next move, authorized silence, stage of practice, likely false stop, and corrective tradition.","Test exact teacher instructions at the point where a practitioner wants to objectify, appropriate, force, possess, or systematize an insight.","Ask dual-trained practitioners whether changing traditions changes the felt moment when inquiry should stop or change form.","Compare stopping rule with verification architecture: does what counts as arrival depend on where inquiry was first told to halt?","Protocol improvement: before using a practitioner method as a research lens, name where that method tells the researcher to stop, and ask what evidence that stopping point may hide."]}
